data.description: This charming, move-in ready, 4-bedroom, 2.5-bathroom house is now available for sale in the desirable Walton County district. Situated on a .41-acre lot in an established neighborhood, this property offers a comfortable and inviting living space. As you approach the house, you'll be greeted by a covered front porch, perfect for enjoying your morning coffee or relaxing in the evening. The fenced-in back yard provides privacy and security for outdoor activities and pets. Inside, you'll find a spacious and well-designed layout. The separate dining room is ideal for hosting family meals or entertaining guests. The kitchen features a convenient island and a breakfast area, making it a great space for casual dining. The living room boasts a cozy fireplace, creating a warm and inviting atmosphere. Upstairs, the vaulted master suite offers a tranquil retreat with its own garden tub, separate shower, and walk-in closets. Additionally, there are three large bedrooms upstairs, providing ample space for family members or guests. This home is located in a quiet neighborhood, offering peace and tranquility while still being conveniently close to Hwy 78 and downtown Monroe. With no HOA restrictions, you have the freedom to personalize your property to suit your needs. Don't miss out on this opportunity to own a beautiful home in a sought-after location. Contact us today to schedule a viewing of 1620 Deer Creek Lane!
